title: Nightly ICE: no errors encountered even though `delay_span_bug` issued

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
So a hello world-esque warp example now ICEs on nightly rust. I'm not sure if the error is down to the incremental compilation warning or the MIR based error output. The errors are pretty wordy... I've also included the full backtrace ### Code Cargo.toml ```toml [package] name = "demo" version = "0.1.0" edition = "2021" # See more keys and their definitions at https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/reference/manifest.html [dependencies] http = "0.2.6" hyper = "0.14.16" nix = "0.23.1" test_bin = "0.4.0" tokio = { version = "1", features = ["full"] } warp = "0.3" ``` ```Rust use warp::Filter; #[tokio::main] async fn main() { let hello = warp::path("hello") .and(warp::get()) .map(|| String::from("Hello")); warp::serve(hello) .run(([127, 0, 0, 1], 18080)) .await; } ``` ### Meta `cargo +nightly --version --verbose`: ``` cargo 1.65.0-nightly (646e9a0b9 2022-09-02) release: 1.65.0-nightly commit-hash: 646e9a0b9ea8354cc409d05f10e8dc752c5de78e commit-date: 2022-09-02 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu libgit2: 1.5.0 (sys:0.15.0 vendored) libcurl: 7.83.1-DEV (sys:0.4.55+curl-7.83.1 vendored ssl:OpenSSL/1.1.1q) os: Ubuntu 18.04 (bionic) [64-bit] ``` ### Error output ``` warning: Error finalizing incremental compilation session directory `/home/daniel/personal/tarpaulin/tests/data/kill_proc/target/debug/incremental/kill_proc-32bke7lab6pj9/s-gdc5hcdmu7-4e8i7i-working`: No such file or directory (os error 2) error: internal compiler error: no errors encountered even though `delay_span_bug` issued error: internal compiler error: broken MIR in DropGlue(DefId(2:2767 ~ core[31aa]::ptr::drop_in_place), Some(warp::hyper::server::conn::spawn_all::State>, warp::filter::FilterFn<[closure@warp::filters::method::method_is<[closure@warp::get::{closure#0}]>::{closure#0}]>>, [closure@src/main.rs:7:14: 7:16]>>::bind_ephemeral<([u8;
